statements: SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs;

SELECT caller_name, phone_number, response_time FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY response_time ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT incident_type FROM emergency_call_logs;
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs;
SELECT caller_name, phone_number FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE incident_type = 'Fire';
SELECT caller_name, incident_type, response_time FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE response_time >= '2022-01-01';

SELECT DISTINCT incident_type FROM emergency_call_logs;
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE caller_name = 'John'
SELECT caller_location, timestamp FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE call_id = 1
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY timestamp DESC
SELECT caller_name, incident_details FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE timestamp > '2022-01-01'
SELECT team_name, team_lead FROM response_teams WHERE availability = true
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE caller_name='John Doe'
SELECT call_id, caller_name, incident_details FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE timestamp >= '2022-09-15' AND timestamp <= '2022-09-30'

SELECT team_name, team_location, COUNT(*) as total_calls FROM response_teams JOIN emergency_call_logs ON response_teams.team_location = emergency_call_logs.caller_location GROUP BY team_name, team_location ORDER BY total_calls DESC
SELECT caller_name, timestamp, AGE(timestamp, current_timestamp) as call_age FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE incident_details LIKE '%fire%'
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs;
SELECT caller_name, phone_number, location FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE timestamp >= '2022-01-01';
SELECT team_id, team_name, team_lead FROM response_teams ORDER BY team_name DESC;
SELECT incident_type, location, timestamp FROM incidents WHERE location LIKE '%hospital%';
SELECT incident_id, incident_type, timestamp FROM incidents ORDER BY timestamp ASC LIMIT 3;
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY timestamp DESC, caller_name ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT caller_name, phone_number, location FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE location LIKE '%Hospital%' AND incident_details IS NOT NULL;
SELECT * FROM response_teams WHERE team_name = 'Medical Team' AND available = true;
SELECT incident_type, location, reporter_name, timestamp FROM incidents ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT caller_name, phone_number, response_time FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE response_time > INTERVAL '10 minutes';
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs LIMIT 5;
SELECT caller_name, call_time, incident_details FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE call_time > '2022-01-01' AND incident_details LIKE '%fire%';
SELECT * FROM responders WHERE specialty = 'Medical' ORDER BY responder_name ASC;
SELECT responder_name, responder_phone FROM responders WHERE responder_phone LIKE '(555)%' AND responder_name LIKE 'Dr%' LIMIT 10;

SELECT incidents.incident_type, response_logs.response_details FROM incidents JOIN response_logs ON incidents.incident_id = response_logs.call_id WHERE incidents.incident_type = 'Fire' AND response_logs.response_time < '01:00:00';
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY call_time DESC;
SELECT caller_name, caller_phone, incident_details FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE call_time > '2021-01-01'
SELECT * FROM responders WHERE specialty = 'Medical' ORDER BY responder_name;
SELECT * FROM incidents JOIN response_logs ON incidents.incident_id = response_logs.call_id WHERE incident_type = 'Fire'

SELECT e.caller_name, r.responder_name, i.incident_type FROM emergency_call_logs e INNER JOIN responders r ON e.caller_name = r.responder_name INNER JOIN incidents i ON e.call_time = i.incident_timestamp
SELECT * FROM emergency_call_logs;
SELECT call_id, caller_name, call_timestamp FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY call_timestamp DESC;
SELECT caller_name, incident_details FROM emergency_call_logs WHERE response_time > 10;
SELECT team_name, team_lead FROM emergency_response_teams WHERE team_size > 5;
SELECT incident_id, incident_type, incident_location FROM incidents WHERE incident_location LIKE '%Highway%';

SELECT call_id, caller_name FROM emergency_call_logs ORDER BY call_timestamp DESC;
SELECT incident_type, incident_location FROM incidents WHERE incident_type='Fire';
SELECT team_name, team_lead, team_size FROM emergency_response_teams WHERE team_location='New York';
SELECT count(*) AS total_calls, MAX(response_time) AS max_response_time FROM emergency_call_logs;
